					<h3>Creator Support Program Policy</h3>

					<p>This Creator Support Program Policy (the "Agreement") is an agreement between the creator who participates in Creator Support Program (the “Creator”) and NAVER WEBTOON CORP. (with its affiliates and subsidiaries, "NAVER WEBTOON" or "We").	Please read Terms of Use, Privacy Policy, and Discovery Policy, and this Agreement (“Terms”) available at <a href="http://www.webtoons.com/en/terms">http://www.webtoons.com/en/terms</a>, before using LINE WEBTOON Website, LINE WEBTOON App.  By participating in Creator Support Program, the Creator agrees to be bound by the Terms.  NAVER WEBTOON may at any time amend the Terms by publishing amended version on LINE WEBTOON Website and/or LINE WEBTOON App.</p>
					<dl>
					<dt><h4>1. What is Patreon and Creator Support Program? </h4></dt>
					<dd>
						<p>Patreon is a way for the creators to earn ongoing funding directly from their fans via crowd-funding. (Learn more about Patreon: <a href="http://www.patreon.com">http://www.patreon.com</a>). The Creator Support Program is a partnership between LINE WEBTOON and Patreon to bring Discover creators a method of monetization. Registering Patreon ID on LINE WEBTOON will enable creators to link their Patreon accounts to their comic series on LINE WEBTOON and let readers pledge directly on WEBTOON. Additionally, WEBTOON will also directly pledge to become a Patron to Discover creators who satisfy the qualifications as specified below.</p>
					</dd>
					<dt><h4>2. Copyright and License</h4></dt>
					<dd>
						<p>The Creator retains the copyright and all of his or her ownership rights in and to the WEBTOON content (“User Posting(s)”), uploaded on LINE WEBTOON Service. The Creator grants NAVER WEBTOON the right to digitally distribute his or her User Postings on Discover and other WEBTOON-related services upon publishing on Discover.</p>
					</dd>
					<dt><h4>3. Duration of Creator Support Program</h4></dt>
					<dd>
						<p>It will begin on 11:00AM EST, August 1, 2016 and end on 11:00AM EST, July 31, 2017.</p>
					</dd>
					<dt><h4>4. Entry Eligibility</h4></dt>
					<dd>
						<p>The Creator must hold a valid creator’s account on Patreon and have it registered on Discover.</p>
					</dd>
					<dt><h4>5. How to Participate in the Program</h4></dt>
					<dd>
						<p>The Creator needs to register a valid Patreon account and have an ongoing series on Discover on LINE WEBTOON service at <a href="http://www.webtoons.com/challenge/publish">[http://www.webtoons.com/challenge/publish]</a> during the period of the Creator Support Program. To enter, please go to <a href="http://www.webtoons.com/challenge/publish">[http://www.webtoons.com/challenge/publish]</a> and follow the step-by-step directions on that page.</p>
					</dd>
					<dt><h4>6. Pledge Qualification</h4></dt>
					<dd>
						<p>WEBTOON will directly pledge every month until July 2017, to creators who meet the three requirements below, for upto 300 creators every month:
						<p>a) Update at least twice a month;<br>b) [Have 3k+ Subscribers AND Have 10k+ US monthly page views / update] OR [Have 5k+ Subscribers AND Have 5k+ US monthly page views / update]<br>* If you have more than one qualified series on Discover, WEBTOON will pledge to the highest performing series.</p>
